The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             The City Diary
                Sub-inspectors Amit Nandi of Shibpur police station and Mangal Das of Bantra police station were suspended for failing to take Padam Prasad Pant, 75, to hospital in time on Wednesday. A departmental inquiry has been ordered against Shibpur police station additional inspector-in-charge Tapan Mukherjee and three constables. Pant fell ill after chasing a bus and died on the road.     Two motorcycle-borne men snatched Rs 36,000 from a security guard near Sech Bhavan in Salt Lake on Friday. Sinha had withdrawn the money from a nationalised bank and was cycling to his office.    A gang of youths took away Rs 70,000 at gunpoint from an electronics shop on Tollygunge Road on Friday evening.    Adhir Mondal was arrested in Salt Lakes EC block on Friday for allegedly molesting a woman labourer.     Calcutta University will start undergraduate courses in industrial chemistry and fashion technology from this year.                                                                                                                                                              
